# 🌍 Customer Intelligence System using Classification, Ensemble Learning & Clustering

## 📌 Project Overview

This project develops an end-to-end **Customer Intelligence System** using Machine Learning techniques. The system performs customer/country segmentation through clustering and predicts segment categories using classification and ensemble learning algorithms.

The project demonstrates the complete machine learning workflow, including data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis (EDA), clustering, classification, model evaluation, and feature importance analysis.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

* Perform exploratory data analysis on country development indicators.
* Segment countries into meaningful groups using clustering techniques.
* Build classification models to predict country segments.
* Compare ensemble learning algorithms for predictive performance.
* Identify the most influential features affecting country development.

---

## 📂 Dataset

The dataset contains socio-economic and health indicators such as:

* Child Mortality Rate
* Exports
* Imports
* Health Expenditure
* Income
* Inflation
* Life Expectancy
* Total Fertility Rate
* GDP per Capita (GDPP)

Dataset Source: Kaggle Country Development Dataset

---

## ⚙️ Project Workflow

### Phase 1: Data Understanding

* Dataset Loading
* Data Inspection
* Missing Value Analysis
* Statistical Summary

### Phase 2: Exploratory Data Analysis & Preprocessing

* Correlation Analysis
* Distribution Analysis
* Outlier Detection
* Feature Scaling
* Data Preprocessing Pipeline

### Phase 3: Customer Segmentation (Clustering)

* K-Means Clustering
* DBSCAN Clustering
* Hierarchical Clustering
* Elbow Method
* PCA Visualization
* Segment Label Generation

Generated Segments:

* Underdeveloped
* Developing
* Developed
* Advanced Economy

### Phase 4: Classification & Ensemble Learning

Models Implemented:

* Decision Tree
* Random Forest
* AdaBoost
* Gradient Boosting
* XGBoost

### Feature Importance Analysis

* GDP per Capita (gdpp)
* Child Mortality (child_mort)
* Total Fertility Rate (total_fer)

---

## 📊 Model Performance

| Model             | Accuracy |
| ----------------- | -------: |
| Decision Tree     |   97.06% |
| Gradient Boosting |   97.06% |
| AdaBoost          |   94.12% |
| XGBoost           |   94.12% |
| Random Forest     |   91.18% |

Best Performing Models:

* Decision Tree
* Gradient Boosting

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn
* Scikit-Learn
* XGBoost
* Joblib
* Google Colab

---


---

## 📈 Key Insights

* GDP per Capita is the most influential factor in determining development segments.
* Child Mortality Rate strongly impacts segmentation.
* K-Means successfully identified meaningful country clusters.
* Ensemble learning models achieved high predictive accuracy.
* Decision Tree and Gradient Boosting provided the best performance with 97.06% accuracy.

